cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new network architecture for the panoptic segmentation task, which involves both semantic and instance segmentation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a parameter-free panoptic head that enables prediction of an extra unknown class, which involves some level of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of deformable convolution and Mask R-CNN, which are common techniques in computer vision and deep learning, respectively, and may suggest the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, including Cityscapes and COCO, which are commonly used in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper does not involve natural language processing (cs.CL) explicitly, but it may be relevant for some aspects of the panoptic segmentation task.
